PROTO2 Project ideas

Game Control System

Hierarchy:
    -Digilab:       Emergency use, ignores rules and permissions and exectues command

    -Discord:       Admin, is allowed to exectues commands and confirms requests from       
                    Minecraft
    
    -Minecraft:     User, can send command requests to the discord bot, which have to be 
                    allowed by a user on discord

Example:            When a Player types a command, for example: request is sent to          
                    discord-bot and needs to be allowed or declined with a command on discord, for example: !confirm or !deny   

Raspberry Pi:       -upon a request being made, it is sent to node-red, on which it gets 
                    sent to both the discord bot, which awaits a response from a user, and the digilab's display should show both the request type and user who requested it. LED could blink to show that a request has been made (turn the LED off with a button -> send message on minecraft saying the request is being worked on)

Digilab:            -The digilab should be used as a way to manually activate commands but 
                    also to get requests. Buttons will be mapped to sepcific commands each.

Discord:            -Gets requests from Node-red, asks user on server (either any or user with specific roles) for permission to 
                    execute said command. 
                    -> Upon accepting: command gets executed
                    -> Upon declining: command doesn't get executed and reason gets sent to the minecraft server (chat)
                    -remote kick and restart commands. other commands such as give or spawn may be implemented.

Node-Red:           -Flow for communication 
                    Discord -> Node-RED -> Minecraft  
                    Buttons -> Node-RED  
                    Node-RED -> LEDs / LCD / Dashboard


Dashboard:          -Shows informations on the server (playerCount, playerNames, isServerUp, errors)
                    -Shows if and which requests are currently waiting approval
                    -Potential button to accept or decline, depends on if request approval is needed from Dashboard
                    and if discord and the digilab aren't enough or fully working. 


